{"title": "No Sympathy Between Mooks", "content": "You can tell an enemy force is downright evil when its members don't even support each other. Sure they have a common goal, but it's every mook for himself. One mook will get injured and go down, the other will mock him and/or kill him. But why stop there? Use his body as a shield! Steal his stuff! Desecrate his body!\n\nThis trope is that an evil mook will not help a fallen comrade. It doesn't count if the one is trying to help the other but cannot.\n\nMay result in If You Die, I Call Your Stuff if the other mooks also loot the body or take his stuff before he dies; Dying Alone if they simply leave him. Compare Enemy Civil War and We ARE Struggling Together. Contrast with A Friend in Need, I Cannot Self-Terminate and I Will Only Slow You Down", "url": "https://tvtropes.org/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/NoSympathyBetweenMooks", "media_links": ["/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Film/SherlockHolmesAGameOfShadows", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Film/PiratesOfTheCaribbeanAtWorldsEnd", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Creator/JRRTolkien", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/TabletopGame/Warhammer40000", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Literature/Animorphs", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Literature/HarryPotter", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Series/BlueBloods", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/VideoGame/CastlevaniaCircleOfTheMoon", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/VideoGame/MarioAndLuigiPartnersInTime", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/VideoGame/ChronoTrigger", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/VideoGame/DoomII", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/VideoGame/WarcraftIII", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/VideoGame/StarCraftII", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/VideoGame/MassEffect3", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/VideoGame/BatmanArkhamCity", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/VideoGame/Borderlands2", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/VideoGame/Touhou", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/VideoGame/FalloutNewVegas", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/WesternAnimation/SamuraiJack"], "non_media_links": ["/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/ItsAllAboutMe", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/KickTheDog", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/DueToTheDead", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/IfYouDieICallYourStuff", "/pmwik